This paper discusses the topic of interpretability in machine learning, which is a common theme in several sub-categories of computer science. However, given the focus on deep neural networks and other nonlinear methods, as well as the emphasis on practical applications, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the mention of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) suggests that these sub-categories are also relevant. Finally, the discussion of potential security risks and attacks on machine learning models (cs.CR) indicates that this sub-category may also be applicable.
